animal.description:
Friends for life, Bear and Pippin are two tiny precious Chihuahuas that need to be adopted as a pair.  They are rarely apart and provide each other immeasurable comfort and companionship.  Both would be wonderful pets for a senior or family with older children.  No small children or puppies, please.  They prefer a calm quiet household where they can take a nap in peace.  Preferably, with someone that is home most of the day.  They like to follow you around the house as you go about your day.  Bear is a feisty five year old boy with a chocolate and white colored coat.  He may only weigh six pounds, but he’s definitely the boss and has a big personality.  His shy girlfriend Pippin is seven years old and a bit on the chunky side at eight pounds.  She’s a tricolored beauty and very calm and sweet.  With daily walks, Pippin should be fit and trim in no time.  Both dogs walk well on leash and enjoy taking trips to the park.  Like most Chihuahuas, they can be selective when making friends with other dogs.  If own a dog currently, we would be happy to schedule a meet and greet to check compatibility.  They are not fond of cats.  The perfect house guests, Bear and Pippin are very well mannered and already housebroken.  A fenced in yard is a must for these two tiny pups to keep them safe when outside.  Bear and Pippin are easy to love and care for.  If you are looking for a package deal, please consider this sweet pair.  

To adopt this pet, Click "More About Us" and then "Adoption Application" to be directed to our online HSNWGA application form.  You will be contacted by our Adoption Coordinator once your application is reviewed and approved.  Due to high volume of applications, we are only able to contact those applicants that best meet the needs of that individual pet.

animal.description: Hi I'm Dexter and I am a sweet, soft and kind puppy. I have an adorable face with ears that stand up and flop at just the right spot. The ears top off my cute fully posed sit while being on guard. I am busy working on my potty training, and not to brag but I can go all night in my kennel without an accident. I would make the perfect companion for any family! Come meet me and fall in love! The "D Pups" came into rescue when they were just a couple weeks old, along with their sweet & beautiful mom, Daisybelle Fluffbottoms, when they became a homeless family and needed our help. Dexter is a growing male Black Lab mix pup born approximately 10-23-20. He is neutered, vaccinated, microchipped, given flea/tick preventive, dewormed & started on heartworm preventive. Adoption fee is $575 to help offset the many expenses we have for vetting costs. We rely strictly on adoption fees and donations to continue to save the lives of orphaned & abandoned pets; 100% goes towards their care. If interested in adopting one of our available dogs or puppies, please complete an online adoption application at https://dollyslegacyanimalrescue.org/adopt/ You will be contacted by our adoption coordinator via email after your application has been reviewed & approved to schedule an appointment.

She is crate trained so can be left alone for a reasonable amount of hours.  She must have a 6ft securely fenced yard and kids must be over 10yrs old.  During foster, all supplies will be provided.

animal.description:
Luka is a very sweet special needs tiny chi, about 10 years old we think and only 7lbs! 

He came to us from another shelter where he was found unable to walk, partially paralyzed and dragging his hind legs. It appears to be an old injury and nothing to be done to fix it at this point but he's a happy little guy not in pain and loves to be carried. He doesn't have control of his bladder and bowels and needs his bladder expressed several times daily (he is very easy and tolerant for it!) and needs someone experienced with caring for special needs pups like him. 

If you are interested in opening your home to this sweetheart please submit an application from our website. He's in the process of getting a full medical work-up with our veterinary team- he has a heart murmur that will require more testing and desperately needs a dental as his teeth are rotting and falling out! Primary Color: Chocolate Secondary Color: White Age: 9yrs 10mths 0wks

I would make the perfect companion for any family! Come meet me and fall in love! The "D Pups" came into rescue when they were just a couple weeks old, along with their sweet & beautiful mom, Daisybelle Fluffbottoms, when they became a homeless family and needed our help. Dexter is a growing male Black Lab mix pup born approximately 10-23-20. He is neutered, vaccinated, microchipped, given flea/tick preventive, dewormed & started on heartworm preventive. Adoption fee is $575 to help offset the many expenses we have for vetting costs. We rely strictly on adoption fees and donations to continue to save the lives of orphaned & abandoned pets; 100% goes towards their care. If interested in adopting one of our available dogs or puppies, please complete an online adoption application at https://dollyslegacyanimalrescue.org/adopt/ You will be contacted by our adoption coordinator via email after your application has been reviewed & approved to schedule an appointment.

animal.description:
It's clear by how emaciated Cedric was upon his arrival to Saving Grace and the scars on his face that he has not always known kindness, however, you would never know based on his happy go lucky personality. Cedric is the kind of dog that makes you wanna be a better person because Cedric only sees the best in others. He's a happy guy that greets you with a wagging tail and a big smile and is an absolute testament to the resilience of dogs. Cedric is enjoying his extra meals and the beefing up process to get him to a healthy weight. Once there he is sure to be a super fun boy that would love to join you on any fun plans you had in mind! Cedric would absolutely love to meet you, so won't you consider giving him the loving, caring home he so deserves?!

Please note we are working with limited staff/volunteers at this time. For full details of our current adoption appointment policy, please see https://savinggracenc.org/adoption-appointments-during-this-time/. Highlights:

We are working with a very limited staff/volunteer base

We do not have the people power to respond to emails/call about specific dogs

Our appointments are limited to 2 people at a time and for a maximum of 30 minutes.

Please arrive at your appointment ready to meet the dogs we have available. At this time, many dogs are in foster families or not yet posted on our website. Be flexible and ready to meet any number of wonderful dogs available onsite at the time of your appointment.

All puppies and dogs at Saving Grace are crate trained, have been spayed/neutered, are up to date on their vaccinations, are on heartworm preventative and have been microchipped. Their adoption fee is $375.00. Each has been carefully screened for disposition and temperament in order to provide your home with a safe companion that will enjoy life as your new family member.

Our Adoption Form can be completed online at our website at https://savinggracenc.org/how-to-adopt/ .

An Adoption Form is required before setting up an appointment to meet with a potential adoptee or a foster home.

Sending an Adoption Form does not commit you to an adoption, it simply provides us with background information on potential homes.

If you'd like to donate to help cover the cost of care for these wonderful dogs awaiting new homes, please visit the donate page on our website at https://savinggracenc.org/donate-now/ .

Saving Grace is a small, non-profit 501-C3 organization operated by volunteers only. Most of our animals come from rural animal control shelters where lack of space and resources limit their time and adoption possibilities. Thank you for choosing Saving Grace! We look forward to helping you find your new companion and family member.

animal.description:
Abby Lynn is a beautiful and trendy doggy, who likes to wear her string of pearls and take the world head-on despite her disabilities; blindness and diabetes. She wasn’t blind her entire life, so her memory is engrained with the beauty that surrounds her.
 
Abby loves to be part of the family! If something is amiss outside, she will let you know! She’s shy at first, but don’t worry, there is a fun and friendly bark just waiting to come out! She will greet you at the door when you arrive home, and sniff the day’s adventures on your clothes, she loves to be near her family.
 
Abby loves going on walks, she also loves treats! Blindness doesn’t stop Abby, and she learns your home layout very quickly. It’s spectacular to see her walk through a room to a hallway, stop, pivot, and walk down the hall without bumping into anything! Obviously this will take some time, but she is very cautious and careful until she learns, and then she becomes carefree. Her day consists of a lot of beauty rest, binging Netflix, and just being sweet and gorgeous. She doesn’t require, nor ask, for a lot of physical attention, but she does enjoy being (slowly)scooped up and loved on.
 
Abby Lynn has diabetes, which just means she’ll need a special diet of healthier food options, twice daily insulin, and the occasional blood sugar testing so the doctor can track her over the phone as opposed to office visits. Since she is diabetic, she does need to go #1 about once an hour during the day, unless she’s in a deep beauty rest or overnight while she’s deep asleep. She will let you know she needs to go outside by simply standing up! Standing up and walking around from a beauty rest can mean one of two things, she thirsty or she needs to go potty! If she begins to walk circles in front of you, you have time and can scoop her up. She will stop if you say no, let’s go outside! 
 
Abby is a girl who knows what she wants. She can be persuaded by kindness and patience, just remember that she is blind and she needs time to understand her surroundings. How does she get when she feels pushed around? She simply sits down right in front of you and refuses to listen.
 
Abby loves having fur friends, but she’s also okay being the sole attention of her family! She doesn’t like the sound of food thieves around her while she eats. She may give them a grimace and low growl, or sometimes an outlandish yelp but she won’t bite or hurt them. She just wants to eat in peace and should be fed separately. 

Giving Abby her insulin is super easy and she doesn’t even flinch. She had diabetes before she lost her eyes and is very used to this routine, plus she gets that treat after! Abby is not toy motivated, they just aren’t of interest to her. She loves fluffy snow! If it’s snowing, get her outside and watch the cuteness begin and she jumps and plays in and out of the snow.
 
Abby Lynn does well with kids and loves to cuddle with them! Our children are over 7, but with her demeanor I would assume it would be just fine! Abby hasn’t met anyone she doesn’t like, and she’s very interested in smelling their clothes and getting to know who they are and where they’ve been that day!
 
Abby Lynn really is a great girl. Yes, she’s diabetic and recently blind, but the beautiful part is that hasn’t stopped her from being truly kind and having a love for life and her family. She just wants to belong, and the perfect family for her would be a family that is just as loving and kind as her; a family who has the time to take her outside on walks, let her outside to go #1 throughout the day, and a family that knows that despite what she’s been through, she is deserving of the love from them as she gives to her family.

Abby’s adoption fee is $125, and adopters must live within 175 miles of the Quad City Area.

For a chance to meet Abby, fill out the online application at www.k9kindnessrescue.org/adopt/application

Abby and K9 Kindness Rescue thank you for considering adoption through rescue for your new family companion!

animal.description: Introducing the beautiful Lana, a 3 year old 46lb gal originally rescued in the aftermath of a hurricane in Louisiana. We met this sweetheart in a Texas shelter and brought her to NYC where she's currently living in a loving foster home. Lana is a very sweet dog in the home, but is very fearful outside and needs a patient adopter who will help her slowly build up her confidence. Lana is initially wary of new people, and is typically more fearful of men at first. But her fosters tell us that by giving her time to herself and going slowly with her, she warms up to her people and is very loving - she's taken to following her current foster around the house and loves snuggling up next to her! Lana is also timid around other dogs and likely wouldn't do well in a home with another very exuberant pup, but she could do well with the right canine match. She responds well to treats and love, and we know that with a little extra patience and time she'll open up to her true happy self! Approved adopters interested in Lana can email adopt@heartsandbonesrescue.com for more info. If you're not approved yet, apply today!

animal.description:
Senior Hearts Rescue and Renewal is the only licensed senior dog rescue organization in Western Pennsylvania. We do not have a shelter or a public facility. ALL of our dogs reside in foster homes in the greater Pittsburgh, PA area. 

We are a 100% volunteer organization. Please respect our volunteers' time. If a dog is listed on PetFinder, he/she IS available for adoption. We cannot reply to messages, phone calls, and emails about a dog until we have received, reviewed, and approved an adoption application. 

Our ADOPTION application is found at www.seniorhearts.org Completing this application is the first step in our adoption screening process. You MUST complete the application in entirety in order to be considered as a potential adopter.  Please select "More About Us" for further details on our adoption requirements.  You can meet a dog ONLY after we have completed our adoption approval process.

If you are looking at the dog below, it most certainly means the dog is available for adoption. We look forward to receiving your application in hopes that you are able to meet our adoption requirements and provide this dog a loving furever home.

Hello. Layla here. I’m 10yrs tough and 29lbs. I’m an independent girl who loves long walks and lots of play time. They call me a “toy destructer”. 

I love to cuddle, snuggle, be held, and get belly rubs. I am very loyal to my person.
  I am an exuberant walker and good for long distances.  I have been told I am very cute, spunky, with a bold personality.  

Apartment living would be a big no, I like to bark at the delivery people.  They love me. 

 I would prefer to be an only child.  No other dogs cats or kids for me. I want and deserve all the attention I can handle. 

If the best of best friends is what you are searching for, you have found your girl.  I promise all the unconditional love you can handle. I can be adopted within a two hour radius of Pittsburgh, PA. If you are interested in giving me a furever home, you must first complete the adoption application at www.seniorhearts.org

xoxo
Layla

animal.description:
One look at our handsome Catahoula mix, Romeo and you'll be reciting William Shakespeare. With his gorgeous blue merle coat and matching set of bright blue eyes he is one gorgeous fella, but just wait till we tell you he has a personality to match! Even though he's a big boy about 65 pounds you won't be convincing him that he's not a lapdog, and he will happily climb up and cuddle up at the first opportunity. He is still warming up to all the hustle and bustle of the farm, and seems to be uncertain and submissive regarding new experiences, but takes comfort in the kindness and encouragement of humans and more confident canines. Romeo would love to find a home with a female canine companion, his very own Juliet if you will. At just two years old, we are sure that once he is comfortable you'll be left with a happy energetic dog as Catahoulas are known for. Romeo would do great in an active family who can ensure he gets plenty of exercise and challenges his mind with training which will also help to continue to build his confidence. We know that you've already fallen head over heels so go ahead and put in your adoption request to come meet Romeo!

Please note we are working with limited staff/volunteers at this time. For full details of our current adoption appointment policy, please see https://savinggracenc.org/adoption-appointments-during-this-time/. Highlights:

We are working with a very limited staff/volunteer base

We do not have the people power to respond to emails/call about specific dogs

Our appointments are limited to 2 people at a time and for a maximum of 30 minutes.

Please arrive at your appointment ready to meet the dogs we have available. At this time, many dogs are in foster families or not yet posted on our website. Be flexible and ready to meet any number of wonderful dogs available onsite at the time of your appointment.

All puppies and dogs at Saving Grace are crate trained, have been spayed/neutered, are up to date on their vaccinations, are on heartworm preventative and have been microchipped. Their adoption fee is $375.00. Each has been carefully screened for disposition and temperament in order to provide your home with a safe companion that will enjoy life as your new family member.

Our Adoption Form can be completed online at our website at https://savinggracenc.org/how-to-adopt/ .

An Adoption Form is required before setting up an appointment to meet with a potential adoptee or a foster home.

Sending an Adoption Form does not commit you to an adoption, it simply provides us with background information on potential homes.

If you'd like to donate to help cover the cost of care for these wonderful dogs awaiting new homes, please visit the donate page on our website at https://savinggracenc.org/donate-now/ .

Saving Grace is a small, non-profit 501-C3 organization operated by volunteers only. Most of our animals come from rural animal control shelters where lack of space and resources limit their time and adoption possibilities. Thank you for choosing Saving Grace! We look forward to helping you find your new companion and family member.

animal.description:
If you don’t want to start from scratch with a puppy and you want a stalwart friend by your side at all times, then an adult dog may be the best choice you ever make. We’ve all heard the phrase, “You can’t teach an old dog new tricks,” but that couldn’t be further from the truth. Adult dogs have a great attention span and eagerness to please, allowing them to learn faster than more youthful members of their species. If you’re looking for a steadfast companion who will be truly grateful for a second chance at a happy life, consider adopting a dog. 

Viv needs more socialization with people and dogs. She would not be a good dog for a first time owner. Training with positive methods needs to start immediately so she can learn a way to communicate in a successful way. Impulse control exercises to help her calm down. Because some body sensitivity to handling was seen, young children are not recommended at this time. High rise buildings with elevators or congested areas would not help her develop good behaviors. They would cause her to get too excited and possibly make poor choices. Work on trade up's for things of higher value. Do not just take things from her. Do not rough house and get her too excited, this is when she will start to jump up and get mouthy. Not too much touchy/feely/kissy/huggy until you have time to develop a relationship and you can tell what she is comfortable with. Seek out a daycare/trainer for dog socialization if you would like to see how much she can improve. Do not just meet dogs on the street. Good socialization with a dog of correct temperament is needed.

Charles is just a hunk, a hunk of burning love! This big guy, approx. 5 years old and 75 lbs, has quickly stolen the hearts of his foster parents and everyone who meets him. Aside from being a real looker, Charles also knows how to turn on the charm. In fact, he sometimes gets to go to work with his foster mom and is a very well-behaved, happy office guest.

Charles is well-behaved and snuggly but also enjoys being active as well, as he is a generally athletic, outgoing, fun guy! He loves going for walks and long hikes, but with his size, needs an able-bodied handler. In the yard, he enjoys romping and exploring along with a good game of fetch.

Charles is housebroken however he can not be crated. His foster parents give him run of the house and he does just fine. Charles loves getting treats in his Kong, however he sometimes loves them a bit too much and will resource guard. The good news is that he is very food motivated and has picked up on commands quickly. Another fun fact: he’s a very good boy at the vet!

Please note that the first step in our process is the adoption application found on our website www.midatlanticbullybuddies.org. Charles is neutered, microchipped and vaccinated.

I am shocked that this amazing girl has not received any applications as of yet. She is an amazing 2-3 year old Bully Blend ! She weighs about 50 pounds and is scheduled for her spay soon! She is full of love and is looking for a family to be her forever and call her own.

She loves to hang with everyone especially her foster mom and the kids who range from 12-22! Boys and girls alike. She loves to play, go for long walks (although she is working on her leash skills), meet new people - she loves everyone, although she likes to jump and give hugs which we are working on so she does not knock anyone down. She loves to watch TV, and chew her Kong and Nylabones. She is doing great in her foster home but needs to be in a home where she can be with her family all of the time. At this time we would not recommend a home with other animals. She is friendly toward them but does not have proper puppy social skills. This is something she needs to work on as she apparently had not had the opportunity as a young puppy to learn these skills. She is completely housebroken and rarely has accidents, if so it is because her foster family missed that she was waiting at the door with leash to go out. Did I forget she also loves car rides ! She does not have any separation anxiety and rarely barks ! She also has the best smooshy nose freckle face and loves to give kisses
She would benefit from a fenced-in yard as she loves to play ball and frisbee! And believe it or not she even brings it back. If you are seeking a forever fur baby please consider Nellie.

animal.description: Hi! My name is Chloe! I was rescued by an animal shelter in South Carolina before arriving at the Big Dog Ranch Rescue. I'm a pretty quiet girl who likes to keep to herself most of the time, but can be talkative at times when other pups are near, particularly while I'm eating. I am not overly social and usually don't like it when other dogs come near my space, so I would probably do best living in a home where I am the only dog around. I think that I could be happy in a home with children, preferably older children who would know to give me some space at times and how to respect my boundaries. I think I'd be an excellent pick for an experienced dog owner who can help me learn how to be more confident in myself and my abilities. I could really be happy in any type of home environment. I could benefit from continued training, including potty-training but I do keep my kennel very clean overnight. I love to go on nice long leashed walks here at the ranch and can't wait to continue doing that with you really soon.

animal.description:
Bella is a 12 year-old, 13 pound, toothless Applehead Chihuahua. Her disposition is very sweet. She loves to cuddle, is curious, and will follow her people all over the house to see what they're up to. She loves to sleep with her person at night. Because she is toothless, she needs soft food. She loves to walk and hike. She can easily walk several miles each day, but will need a lift with any tall steps. Bella has never been trained by crate, but knows to eliminate outside. She does occasionally have accidents inside when she's stressed. Because of her small size, she is afraid of shadows when outside at night, and may need some assurance that's its safe to go into the yard. Bella's parents believed her to be empathic in nature, and very aware of their health. Her elderly parents suffered from

diabetes and secondary ailments, for which Bella seemed to express an innate awareness if their sugars were off, or if they needed help.

Bella will do best in a home where she is the only pet, only because that's been her experience throughout her life. She is good with families, but will enjoy older kids and adults best.

animal.description:
Imagine your home with the loveliest pair of puppy dog eyes looking back at you from every room. The best part about adopting a puppy is seeing them enjoy all of the new things the world has to offer. They will need time, energy, and patience to help them become the best family pets they can be, so if you’re up for a challenge and a lot of fun, consider adopting one! 

Steel, although adorable is not for a first time dog owner. He will need someone experienced in crate training. He did not do well when adopted for a short time when left alone. He is a rough/pushy player with other dogs and barks a lot when playing with them. He will need a play partner that is comfortable with this. Start training class as soon as you get him home so he understands what to do to be successful. He would not do well in a congested building or elevator building. Because he may take a while to settle in a crate your neighbors must be tolerant of a barking/howling puppy.

Callie is a 2-year-old Catahoula Leopard Mix, at least that's our best guess! She is so beautiful, it's quite a mystery.
Fun Fact: The Catahoula Leopard is the state dog of Louisiana.
 
Callie is an incredibly loyal, intelligent, and playful pup. She loves to be by your side, and (unless absorbed in the chewing of her favorite bone) will respond very quickly and cheerily to your call.
She needs to be walked regularly, or else she will get restless and start scratching at furniture and rugs. This is because Catahoula Leopards are working dogs, and were trained to hunt wild pigs and herd farm animals. Due to her herding instinct, she will usually stay close to your side if you are out and about. Since EVERY dog should have daily exercise, this should be no problem!
Callie doesn’t trust strangers, whether they be adult humans that she doesn’t know or other dogs. She’s not violent towards them, unless she feels like the house is being threatened. She will bark at people who approach the property.
She loves to play and will often bark while wagging her tail and jumping around, which can seem confusing to some who think this seems aggressive. Be careful what you give her to play with though, because she loves to tear up her toys (although very rarely tears up anything not given to her). Bones are a favorite of Callie's and provide a perfect way for her to chew away safely.
Her crate training has proven to be exceptional. She may bark or whine at first as she gets settled into your home, but she is very good once she feels comfortable in the space.
Callie is awaiting her forever home and is enjoying her time and learning to be part of a family while she waits !
animal.name: Callie

animal.description:
Senior Hearts Rescue and Renewal is the only licensed senior dog rescue organization in Western Pennsylvania. We do not have a shelter or a public facility. ALL of our dogs reside in foster homes in the greater Pittsburgh, PA area. 

We are a 100% volunteer organization. Please respect our volunteers' time. If a dog is listed on PetFinder, he/she IS available for adoption. We cannot reply to messages, phone calls, and emails about a dog until we have received, reviewed, and approved an adoption application. 

Our ADOPTION application is found at www.seniorhearts.org Completing this application is the first step in our adoption screening process. You MUST complete the application in entirety in order to be considered as a potential adopter.  Please select "More About Us" for further details on our adoption requirements.  You can meet a dog ONLY after we have completed our adoption approval process.

If you are looking at the dog below, it most certainly means the dog is available for adoption. We look forward to receiving your application in hopes that you are able to meet our adoption requirements and provide this dog a loving furever home.

And a short message from Abby...

Hey, there big beautiful world!  My name is Abby and I am a 13 years young gal looking for her furever home.  I only weigh 7 pounds so you could take me everywhere with you.  I am blind but that doesn't stop me from doing anything a dog can do with vision.

I love short walks. I love soft toys to play with when I am in the mood. I wouldn't mind a dog sibling but it is not a must.  I get a bit bossy with them.  I love all people and especially my person.  I will follow you where ever you go.  

If a best friend is what you are looking for then I am your girl.  I promise soooo much unconditional love that you can handle. I can be adopted within a two hour radius of Pittsburgh, PA. If you are interested in giving me a furever home, you must first complete the adoption application at www.seniorhearts.org

xoxo
Abby

animal.description:
Meet Freckles! She is a fun, 27 lb, female heeler-mix. We think she is about 9 months old. Freckles is house trained and knows basic commands like sit, down, leave it, and come. She is learning to fetch. She needs some more training but learns quickly and is an overall great dog. I've never seen her be aggressive with anyone. Wonderful with kids. She gets along with other dogs. Don't know about cats. She loves and needs daily exercise. Walks well on a leash. Sleeps in her crate but doesn't really like it. She loves chew toys, treats, and her stuffed animal. 

She is from Pinon, AZ but has lived with her foster family in Flagstaff, AZ for the past month. She is spayed and has her rabies shots, parvo shots, and boosters. She is a healthy, happy, energetic girl! She would do best with lots of attention and companionship- human and/or dog. She must have learned about couches in her past life because she LOVES hanging with her family on the couch. She sheds minimally. Good with bikes. Okay with water. Must have a fenced yard. Meet your adventure dog!  

Adoption adoption applications can be done online at blackhathumanesociety.org

McKinley's ideal home would be a single women, retired or works from home, who can give him round the clock attention and doesn't travel often. He loves to snuggle and play and his heavily attached to "his person". He loves squeaky toys and carries them around everywhere he goes. 

He would do best in a home with no cats, no kids, no men, and not regular visitors. Also, no other dogs is preferred but he can coexist with submissive dogs similar in size or slightly larger. He must go to a home with experience handling aggressive dogs; applications who has not had first hand experience with aggressive dogs of their own will not be considered. 

McKinley will never be a dog ho can happily visit with strangers or spend extended periods in a public setting. His life prior to coming to us set him up to file and was not the friendliest. Although he's come a long way he does have his issues and quite the attitude. McKinley will need weeks if not months to fully adjust to your lifestyle. We are asking that he stays within an hour of his foster to help his transition and to provide any support he may need. 

McKinely's separation anxiety has made potty training very difficult. He also does not handle being crated very well and has destroyed numerous crates attempting to get out.

animal.special_needs_notes:
Medical issues: Chronic eye irritation, inflammation and dry eye-requires life long medication twice daily and cleaning of the eyes two to three times a day.
Chronic ear infections and inflammations- requires life long daily cleaning and potentially regular medications for flareups.
Seasonal allergies- requires twice daily oral allergy medications during flare ups (spring through fall)
Severe separation anxiety currently on medications to help him cope, does not handle periods more than two hours away from "his person".

Behavioral issues to be aware of: McKinley hates strangers. All sizes, ages and colors. He without a doubt has a "bite first and ask questions later" kind of attitude. He does generally give a slight growl as a warning but will lunge and grab hold of any body part he can. 

He does resource guard-water and dry food are usually hit or miss with people. Bones, wet food and chews are more valuable to him and he will charge to protect them. His squeaky toys are his highest value item. He has crossed a room to remind someone it's HIS toy.

animal.description: You can fill out an adoption application online on our official website.Vader is a 1-year-old mastiff/lab mix looking for his forever home. He came to ODAAT as a VERY sick puppy infected with Parvo. We honestly didn't know if he would make it, but Vader had the fight in him to survive. Today he is one happy and healthy puppy! Vader is a good mix of playful and calm. He loves to snuggle up on the furniture or in bed at night. He also plays well with the other dogs in his foster home and takes cues from them when they don't want to play anymore. He would do best with another dog in the home that he can play with and continue to learn from. He has not been cat tested at this time. Vader is protective of his family and needs a moment to warm up to people. That big ole mastiff barks can be intimidating! Once he sees you mean him no harm he is a lover. He loves to carry a stick or rocks in his mouth on his walks. So you have to be careful. True to the mastiff breed, he has already started his slobbering skills so he will need his new family to be accepting of this because he owns it! Applications are available on our website www.onedogatatime.us

animal.description:
Wrinkles was found as a stray in Virginia in bad shape. We don't know her history but we can see from her scars that she had it rough. She was in the shelter for several months. We pulled her once they were considering euthanasia due to time.  Wrinkles's eyes ruptured at some point in her past. They were full of infection when we got her. I cannot imagine the pain. She's currently on antibiotic eye drops till surgery. She is covered in scars from fighting dogs, even her body. She's had multiple litters. She is heartworm negative, spayed, and microchipped. She's had multiple negative fecals. Her skin infection is healed. She could definitely benefit from medicated baths though. She's had numerous exams. She had good bloodwork. She's up to date on vaccinations, heartworm prevention, and flea prevention. She is scheduled to have what's left of her eyes removed on February 1st. The estimate is $1,200. She will be able to go home after this. We'd really like to have her pre adopted. She has started licking her forearms from stress. She is scared being around all the dogs. I cannot even imagine hearing all the noises and not being able to see anything. She will growl if the dogs come up to her kennel. But she really likes dogs while walking. She gets very excited over them. There was an incident where a small dog got in her kennel at the same time as her. He's bad about doing that and then growling if you try to get him out. She reacted by biting. We don't blame her. The injury was very small. If she wanted to hurt him she could have. There was a huge size difference. We'd like to have her as an only pet or with a calm single dog. She's obviously had a lot of trauma in her past and she deserves a very quiet home.  
Wrinkles has really come into a wonderful personality. I can't even imagine how amazing she will be once she has her own home with less animals. She loves to go on walks in the neighborhood. She loves all the smells. She's walked past other dogs that she didn't know and could care less. She's very affectionate. She will rarely jump on you all excited. She will give kisses and wants to be petted. She's very happy. She wags a lot. She wants to play with the dogs she meets outside in the yard. She randomly doesn't like the pigs. 

We believe she's mostly shar pei but has a little of something else in there. She's 50 lbs. The vet believes she's 4 years old. Her teeth are sparkling white. She is crate trained. The few times she's been free she's not pottied inside. She's been great in the car. She's not big on being outside in the cold. She wants right back inside. She's good with clothes. 
She is located in New Orleans, Louisiana but we adopt out of state.

animal.description:
Bonded Saluki pair from Quatar.  Must be adopted together. Sweet and gentle. Grew up in the streets of Quatar and a construction site.  40 lbs long legged beauties. Cannot go to a home with invisible fence.

Sugar, spice, and everything nice!
Hope and Angel are a two for one special, they’re attached at the hip so it’s like having just one dog with double the bark!  
They are both Saluki mixes. Hope is black/ brown and 11 months old. Angel is the blonde one and a year and four months old. 
Hope and Angel are both potty trained, cat friendly, dog friendly, people friendly, and love to show affection.  Hope is more outgoing; she loves to snuggle and I mean, really loves to snuggle.  Angel also loves pets and dog piling; however, she enjoys lounging around by herself.  They have an extremely calm temperament and are slowly getting used to the colder weather so they don’t like being outside for long. If you leave your shoes out, they’re safe with them!  Only a few times they’ve picked up a shoe but that habit has been broken.  Both are decent with the crate, will have no issues as this takes time and already on the right track.  
Lastly, Hope is more protective of the house, she will not attack anyone as she loves people so she WILL let you know when someone is at the front door.  Angel loves people so much that when out she’ll howl and whimper instantly but will stop once she has calmed down; this is also a habit that is being reduced but it just takes some time and love! 
Both of these girls will need slow introductions to any other pets in the home as they will be nervous in their new environment. Hope and Angel will have no issues bonding into any loving family!

If interested in adopting please fill out our no obligation online application at www.puppypawsrescue.org 

Note: Our rescue requires that all adopter's current and prior animals are up-to-date on vaccinations (DHLPP & Rabies)  and preventatives (heartworm and flea and tick), unless there is a medical reason not allowing it. All animals in your household should be spayed or neutered unless medically indicated that they should not be or are currently still too young.

Meet our wonder-mom, Atreyu! She is an amazing hound mix momma to not one, not two..but a dozen beautiful babies! Her sweet pups are not old enough to say goodbye so mom can find her forever home. Atreyu is ready to be loved and have all of the attention, and boy does she deserve it!

Her foster family has learned a lot about her. We think she is between one and two years old, as she seems to still be a puppy herself. She is housebroken (only a few accidents, which is normal for any new mom-let alone a home of twelve!) and she is bell-trained. Atreyu is good with dogs ( but probably need slow introduction), ignores our cats, and loves people. She is crate-trained (although she prefers to sleep in a bed with her humans). We are working on her leash skills. she knows sit and appears to be very smart and picks up on things quickly. Atreyu is very playful and loves to snuggle and hug, too.
She loves her two human foster sisters and would do well with any size family.

I have one job (that I don't get paid for) its to set these dogs up to succeed. I'm very blunt, very honest and overprotective. As I'm sitting here writing Omegas ads I need you to know I love this dog so much I would assume keep him then to adopt to him to the wrong home.
 Omega is a big goofy love that doesn't know his own size. He has no idea that he can hurt you. He is very vocal and voices his opinions all day every day. Lol. I've literally seen this dog scare the crap out of people. Funny but not funny. 
 Omega was a owner surrender to the shelter. They paid a high price for him as a puppy and truly cared for him. They taught him sit, shake and lay. What they didn't teach him was manners. They didn't raise a puppy to grow up and be a 90lb all muscle dog. Now let's hit the bullet points.
Omega was raised with kids but is rough and doesn't know his own size. Sensative babies will not do well.
Omega was raised with a Cane Corso but is a attention hog. Submissive females will do good with him.
Omega has a high prey drive. No cats or small pets. Fenced in yard required. 
Omega thinks he belongs in your lap if you get hurt easily stop dont keep reading. 
 Omega is housebroken and crate trained.  Hes beast on a leash. He is 2.5 yrs old, neutered, microchipped,  utd on shots, heartworm negative and on flea/heartworm prevention. 200 adoption fee located in Picayune Ms please pm For Bullies Sake Bully Breed rescue if your qualified and have read the ad.

Armani is a 70-pound cuddle bug couch potato. She loves walks, but does tend to pull. She will settle to a manageable walk is not stimulus is present, as she is extremely excitable by small animals (SQUIRREL!) and keenly alert to any other dogs. Armani has shown some undesirable behavior around some other dogs, so it would be best if she was the only pet in the home. She is however very friendly with people and openly welcomes visitors into the home-sometimes she is too friendly, so we are working on her jumping. Armani does well with children; she is currently in a. foster with tweens and a toddler and had had no issues.

Armani has extreme anxiety when being boarded, likely due to spending time in a shelter. She also has some seasonal allergies, which are easily managed with OTC allergy meds. Armani is a loyal and very affectionate dog who sometimes does not know her own strength. She would be best in a relaxed home with no other animals, a large yard and a tall fence. Armani needs a family who is willing to work with her on learning her strength and being obedient. She knows sit, stay, come and up-but needs to learn how to focus. Armani is just a. big, beautiful potato who deserves a great home.

animal.description:
Update from his foster as of Dec 27, 2020:

He is a very sweet boy. Prefers women but is skittish around men as well as strangers. Is good with kids as long as he is supervised. He gets puppy excited and plays too rough for kids under 10. But if youre present he stays in check. He like to give kisses to my 3 year old and belly rubs.

Finally house broken, kennel trained, no longer jumps on you and finally loads and unload in and out of the vehicle. Knows sit and come. Walks great on a leash if you have him on a pinch collar. If you stop while walking due to people or cars, he complies with the well with the command until distraction has passed.

Still working on his chewing and digging. He does have separation anxiety which is the cause of most of his chewing. Also working on not darting out the front door with the stay command.

Low toy or ball drive. reactive to small creatures aka squirrels in the yard lol. No food or treat aggression. Does not like getting in the bath but once hes in hes good to go.

Will be great for any woman handler! He has great potential. Also shows signs of potential in scent work.

Thunder, and his brother Lightening, were pulled from an animal shelter in Carrolton, TX. Thunder is a little more reserved than his brother; he prefers to get to know you before opening up, but once he does, he's a goof ball. He's very food motivated and tries hard to please his human, no matter what the circumstance. Although he's not terribly concerned with tennis balls (low-to-moderate drive), and seems indifferent to cats, he can be a little dog reactive at times. He also very much likes to eat-he can be a little piggy if allowed, so you'll want to make sure that portion control is a thing with him to prevent him from getting a little too large. Otherwise, he's a very sweet boy. He does have just a bit of separation anxiety-which manifests into some semi-negative behaviors, such as unwanted chewing. Fortunately, he is easily corrected and his foster mom is working hard on reinforcing things for this young man. He's got lots of love to give-perhaps he's the right fit for you and you'll be his new human?

If you are interested in adopting Captain, please complete an application at this link https://petstablished.com/adoption_form/24689/generic . 

We are an official 501C3 organziation that does not have a physical location. Our home address is in Michigan, however, the majority of our dogs are not located in Michigan. The physical location of each our our dogs is posted with the name of the pet or in the title area. If you are within 4 hours of the pet, please be prepared to pick the pet up. We do provide transport assistance, however, the applicant must drive 50% of the total distance of the transport. 

The information that we have available is in our posting. If you would like to discuss this animal additionally please fill out this application. Applications that are completed in our process and being considered as a match will speak to the foster home to gain more information about our adoptable dog.

animal.description:
Gypsy is a beautiful, shy, incredibly loveable 6-7-year-old German Shepherd. She needs a kind gentle person who will appreciate how sensitive and loving she is.

Her owner used her for breeding then surrendered her to a shelter in Arkansas a few months ago when he could no longer care for her. Gypsy was terrified at the shelter and very skittish. It was obvious that she was not socialized or given much attention or affection in her previous home. She seems more comfortable around dogs than people and has a lot of confidence building to do. When she's scared she tries to hide, but in a short time she has come so far! She adores her person and is a constant shadow. She's on the smaller side, only about 55 pounds. Her ears are so expressive! You can always tell when she's happy, scared or alert. Her big sad eyes will melt your heart and the first time she gives you kisses you're basically a puddle on the floor.

Gypsy is spayed, vaccinated in microchipped. We are currently treating her for heartworms and her adopter would need to bring her for her final treatments in February and keep her activity low until her treatment is completed. Her adoption fee is $250 and you can apply for her on our website at: https://rescueofhope.com/adoption-application/

animal.description:
Meet Petey! Petey is an adorable tri-color,  8 lb. chihuahua. He is 4 years old, and does great around other dogs. He definitely enjoys his people cuddles. Petey is outgoing and loves attention. He rides well in the car and would love to go for walks with you. He’s small and easy to carry around. We don’t yet know if he’s housetrained as he in still in boarding.  Petey is heartworm positive so he needs to be adopted on the Tulsa or OKC area so we can continue his life-saving treatment. OWR will cover the cost of his treatment. 
If you have a warm lap, Petey might just be the dog for you. He is looking for his life long cuddle buddy!
If you’d like to meet Petey, the first step is to complete and submit an adoption application on our okwestierescue.com website and we’ll get the process started. 
Please allow 1-2 weeks to finish processing your application, but please know our volunteers are working hard on it. 
Petey’s adoption fee is $300 and is tax deductible. 

NOTE: You must complete and submit an application and be approved to adopt prior to being able to meet the dog.  The requested tax-deductible adoption donation is $400 for our puppies, $300 for up to age 7 and $150 for ages 8 and older.
We do not ship our pets.  Be prepared to travel to Tulsa, OK, or Oklahoma City, OK, or the location where this dog is fostered to pick up your dog in person if your application is approved.  Once you are approved, you may adopt any of our dogs that is a good fit. 
We are a non-profit organization that spends our adoption fees and donations on vaccinations, surgeries, various medical tests, medicines, food and supplies needed by our dogs. Our fees do not cover the overall expenses incurred by the care of our dogs, but they do help defray the costs involved.  We thank you for your support. 
Please Note: We are a RESCUE, which is different from a shelter. We conduct veterinary and personal reference checks during the application approval process. We always try to select the right applicant for each dog, based on the dog’s needs and try to find the best match for both dog and human.
We leave a dog’s profile online until either it has been adopted, has received several applications, or is not able to be adopted for some reason.

animal.description:
If you enjoy pittie wiggles, you'll love Luna Mae! 

Luna Mae has spent over a year in a Texas shelter and she is ready for her forever home. She's a big cuddle bug and will need someone to fulfill her lap dog dreams. Luna is a medium energy dog who will want structured walks with her new adopter. She can join a home with kids over 12 who have experience with big goofy dogs. Luna is currently enjoying the good life in her foster home and working on her manners. She'd love to continue working on her training with you! 

She is up to date on vaccines according to her age, she has received proper deworming, and comes with additional dewormer. She is microchipped, spayed, comes with 1-6 months of preventatives, one month free trial of pet insurance, all of our animals receive a health certificate (this states a licensed veterinary saw the pet and deemed it healthy for travel, it is not a promise of perfect health.) Our transports are USDA certified and tfransport is included in adoption fee of $375!

She is currently being fostered in Houston, Tx but will be traveling to the PNW as soon as she finds her perfect home!

Please inquire by submitting an application to brianna@threelittlepittiesrescue.org

Please fill out an application to be considered :https://petstablished.com/adoption_form/29415/generic

animal.description:
Gypsy is a beautiful, shy, incredibly loveable 6-7-year-old German Shepherd. She needs a kind gentle person who will appreciate how sensitive and loving she is.

Her owner used her for breeding then surrendered her to a shelter in Arkansas a few months ago when he could no longer care for her. Gypsy was terrified at the shelter and very skittish. It was obvious that she was not socialized or given much attention or affection in her previous home. She seems more comfortable around dogs than people and has a lot of confidence building to do. When she's scared she tries to hide, but in a short time she has come so far! She adores her person and is a constant shadow. She's on the smaller side, only about 55 pounds. Her ears are so expressive! You can always tell when she's happy, scared or alert. Her big sad eyes will melt your heart and the first time she gives you kisses you're basically a puddle on the floor.

Gypsy is spayed, vaccinated in microchipped. We are currently treating her for heartworms and her adopter would need to bring her for her final treatments in February and keep her activity low until her treatment is completed. Her adoption fee is $250 and you can apply for her on our website at: https://rescueofhope.com/adoption-application/

animal.description:
Meet Petey! Petey is an adorable tri-color,  8 lb. chihuahua. He is 4 years old, and does great around other dogs. He definitely enjoys his people cuddles. Petey is outgoing and loves attention. He rides well in the car and would love to go for walks with you. He’s small and easy to carry around. We don’t yet know if he’s housetrained as he in still in boarding.  Petey is heartworm positive so he needs to be adopted on the Tulsa or OKC area so we can continue his life-saving treatment. OWR will cover the cost of his treatment. 
If you have a warm lap, Petey might just be the dog for you. He is looking for his life long cuddle buddy!
If you’d like to meet Petey, the first step is to complete and submit an adoption application on our okwestierescue.com website and we’ll get the process started. 
Please allow 1-2 weeks to finish processing your application, but please know our volunteers are working hard on it. 
Petey’s adoption fee is $300 and is tax deductible. 

NOTE: You must complete and submit an application and be approved to adopt prior to being able to meet the dog.  The requested tax-deductible adoption donation is $400 for our puppies, $300 for up to age 7 and $150 for ages 8 and older.
We do not ship our pets.  Be prepared to travel to Tulsa, OK, or Oklahoma City, OK, or the location where this dog is fostered to pick up your dog in person if your application is approved.  Once you are approved, you may adopt any of our dogs that is a good fit. 
We are a non-profit organization that spends our adoption fees and donations on vaccinations, surgeries, various medical tests, medicines, food and supplies needed by our dogs. Our fees do not cover the overall expenses incurred by the care of our dogs, but they do help defray the costs involved.  We thank you for your support. 
Please Note: We are a RESCUE, which is different from a shelter. We conduct veterinary and personal reference checks during the application approval process. We always try to select the right applicant for each dog, based on the dog’s needs and try to find the best match for both dog and human.
We leave a dog’s profile online until either it has been adopted, has received several applications, or is not able to be adopted for some reason.

animal.description:
Hello handsome! Poncho is a 2 year old neutered male hound/boxer mix who weighs 55 lbs. Poncho was rescued from a high kill shelter after being found as a stray. We could not believe that no one came forward to claim this gorgeous guy as their own, but we were happy to give him the second chance he was in desperate need of. Poncho is a total showstopper - his sleek coat, floppy ears, and forehead wrinkles make us SWOON! He is a happy-go-lucky pup who has a zest for life - he is sure to bring a whole lot of fun and laughter to his future home! Poncho is great with other dogs and loves to pal around with his canine friends. Unfortunately, he needs a home without cats. Poncho loves putting his hound nose to work outside, exploring all the interesting smells the great outdoors has to offer. He needs to learn some leash walking skills and manners, but he seems smart and eager to please. We cannot wait for Poncho to find an amazing family that will love and commit to him forever! Could that be yours?

Interested in adopting? Take the first step and complete an adoption application on our website: https://www.all4pawsrescue.com/
We are a foster based organization, so we do not have a facility to visit. Please read our FAQs to learn more: https://www.all4pawsrescue.com/faq
Follow us on Facebook for foster updates and a full list of our adoptable pets: https://www.facebook.com/all4pawsrescue/

animal.description:
*Due to concerns surrounding COVID-19, we have reformatted the way that we do adoptions in order to follow social distancing protocols. We are thrilled that so many people want to adopt right now, but we are not equipped to handle the large number of calls, applications, and email inquiries we are receiving. We are no longer answering phone calls and are doing all communications with adopters via email. If you have a dog you are interested in adopting, please fill out an application before sending us emails. When your application has been processed, you will receive an email from us with further instructions on how to adopt. You do not need a new application for every dog that you are interested in adopting. 

At MAMCO we understand that in order to continue rescuing moms and babies, we must stretch our finances as far as we are able. For this reason we use variable adoption pricing. By assigning higher adoption fees to high demand moms and puppies, we are able to rescue more families in need.The money raised through these adoptions acts as a benefactor to moms and puppies in our care who require expensive veterinary treatments, have behavioral issues, or need more time to find a home. We often reduce the adoption fees on these harder-to-place moms and puppies to help them find forever families. Adoption fees vary, but all include spay or neuter, microchip, up to date vaccinations and deworming, rabies vaccine at the time of spay or neuter, and 30 days of pet insurance. We also cover hernia repair and cherry eye repair at the time of spay or neuter. Applications can be filled out at mamcorescue.org.

animal.description:
Mossimo is a spunky pittie mix who’s estimated to be about 4 years old and was found as a stray. The suburban shelter that found him determined soon after that he is heart worm positive. On top of that, he has a series of other medical issues including a scar on his cornea, Lyme disease, and crusty patches of skin from having fleas prior to arriving at the shelter. 

Despite everything going on with him, he is still a very happy go lucky boy and loves affection. He will crawl up in your lap and try to get as close to you as possible, and when you stop petting him, he will lick your hand to let you know that you weren’t allowed to stop yet. While he loves all of the attention, he’s also surprisingly good at knowing when to just lay down and enjoy the company.

No matter what’s happening, he always has a smile on his face and gives the best hugs and kisses! He absolutely loves all dogs and people! He was also cat-tested initially at the shelter and was curious but not threatening. He hasn’t been tested with children yet but based on how much he loves EVERYONE he meets, we think he’d be fine with older children, but are happy to test him if you’re interested. 

Mossimo will make a great road trip companion! He sits happily in the back seat like a good boy and may occasionally ask for pets, but he’s pretty polite about it. He loves climbing the snow piles outside, so he would also make a good hiking buddy! When he’s not going places, he enjoys chomping on some bones and being the best meatball he can be. 

His foster mom says he’s the easiest dog! He already knows sit, come, settle, and stay commands! He is fully potty trained and attaches to his humans quickly. He is still working on his crate training but is improving. He’s also learning that as much as he wants to be close to his people, jumping on them is a no-no, which is why we suggest only older kids for him until he learns that 60lbs of jumping meathead is not always a good thing no matter how cute you are!

We have multiple applications for Mossimo. Apps are now closed.

animal.description:
Tarzan has the sweetest disposition that is completely opposite of what he has experienced in his previous life. He is so full of love and is so empathetic. He noticed I was crying and began to give me kisses to show me love and make me feel better. He is so enthusiastic with his love and he has so much energy. 

He is definitely going to need someone who understands his strength and is willing to be patient as he learns his manners. Even with his obvious past, he loves all dogs. My chihuahua mixed was so scared and barked at him for 5 minutes straight, yet Tarzan ran by him and ignored him to go play with my other dog. When we went to Petco, a small dog growled at him and he just wanted to lick it while wagging his tail. 

Cats are an absolute no. I believe that in his previous life, he was given positive reinforcement to attack cats. He gets hyperfocused on cats that even after attempts of being redirected with food, treats, and toys, he will have to be physically restrained. After releasing my hug around his chest, he still wanted to push against the fence to find the cat. 

He would be wonderful in a home that understands and can physically handle his strength. He is currently underweight due to his previous life and is already so strong (I do crossfit and he is definitely a workout). When he relaxes at home, he loves to cuddle and he is just the sweetest. He may be taught to be ok around little children, but due to his size and energy, he may knock down little ones unintentionally.

animal.description:
Coco T. is a perky and affectionate 12-year-old female German Shepherd Dog (GSD) who was surrendered to Thulani by the owner. Her previous owner described her as being very friendly to dogs, adults and children.

Coco is delicately affectionate and is not a resource hoarder- she will leave food behind if she's had enough and doesnt seem interested in toys.

Coco has amazing stamina and is in great health. This is a girl who will trot with you as far as you want to go, as many times as you want to go. She would especially thrive in a home where she can be walked/jogged a few times a day.

Coco spent her time outside in a kennel with a companion dog but is housebroken. The foster reports that she has had no accidents indoors where she prefers to be with her humans. She is not a barker or a runner- she likes to lie near the front door but will back away to wait for it to open and makes no effort to leave until the leashes come out. She also likes to hang out in her crate when not going out.

It is obvious that Coco was loved, trained and taken care of by her previous owner and she is looking forward to having a new owner to love and take walks with. 

Thulani Senior German Shepherd Rescue has taken over care for Coco. She is a beautiful girl who will now receive the medical care she needs. Although she has a stiff gait, she is quite mobile and very much loves human interaction. TSGSR will look for a new family with time to love to this wonderful dog. 

Coco T. Summary:
- Female, 12 yrs old, weighs 63 lbs, current on shots
- Good with Adults, dogs, and travels well in the car
- Good with children
- TBD with cats 
 

Coco passed a set of evaluation tests before being accepted into the TSGSR. The tests are not intended to assess how smart the dog is but are important for TSGSR to determine if the dog is expected to be safe in a family home. The tested behaviors check to see if the dog will guard or protect food or toys from people, will tolerate handling all over its body (including ears, nose, lips to check teeth, lifting paws, belly, back, and gently pulling the tail) and the ability to get along with other well behaved dogs. Coco remained calm during all of these tests and showed no aggressive tendencies. As a result, she was accepted into the TSGSR program. 

Please join us in welcoming Coco to TSGSR! Check back often. We will be updating her bio as we learn more about her!

What's Next for Coco T.:
Thulani Senior German Shepherd Rescue (TSGSR) will continue to see that Coco is well cared for and receives all medical care needed for her well being while in our care. In addition, TSGSR is beginning a search for an adoptive home that will care for her for the rest of her life. Coco will come to her new home with a supply of food, a cushy pad if wanted, and other goodies such as toys. 

Cocos medical expenses will be covered for the rest of her life by Thulani Senior German Shepherd Rescue (TSGSR)!

If you want to learn more about Coco, or are interested in possibly providing an adoptive or foster home, please send us a message by clicking on the "Ask About Me" button. We will often get feedback or "updates" from a dog's foster home and as any updates become available they will be included here.

If you are reading about her on Petfinder.com sometimes an available YouTube video is not listed. If this occurs you can still view the video by pasting its URL into a new browser window or tab.
Available Video URL(s): https://youtu.be/rswhDNZMcGU

Saving one dog wont change the world. It will change the world for that one dog.

animal.description:
Mia is looking for a FOSTER or FOSTER-TO-ADOPT home on the NE/NE CO/WY area ASAP

Mia

Located in Dalton NE
5ish years old 
Beagle and Aussie fusion is our best guess
Super dog friendly
Cats unknown
Good with kids with dog manners
House trained 
Crate trained and knows some commands
She's up to date on vaccines but she still needs to be spayed 
Needs a dental
SUCH A HYSTERICAL PERSONALITY
Needs some bumps and lumps removed 
Heartworm positive but on slow kill treatment 
LOVES to be outside 
30lbs 

Mia has had a REALLY rough go on this planet. One look at her and you know she's just been though hell. She has scars all over, her hair loss is legit but one look in her sky blue eyes and you see the stunning girl she truly is. She is so sassy and such a fantastic personality she is impossible not to love once you meet her. She also gives the best facial expressions, she keeps a smile on my face all day. Mia was found by a young girl after having been dumped on the TX/Mexico border. The girl thought that proper animal ownership was just keeping them outside with food and water, she said she didn't even know they needed vaccines . She ended up pregnant suffering from horrible flea allergies, she's Heartworm positive, has significant hair loss and likely cancerous lumps and bumps. Some of her hair is slowly growing back but she's very much a work in progress. She will be spayed, have her lumps and bumps removed and likely a skin biopsy. We will assess her teeth at that time. Unfortunately after we got her to safety she became ill with a REALLY dangerous strain of URI and ended up giving it to her puppies who one by one all passed away. This was completely devastating, however Mia surviving was the silver lining of the situation. We transported her up to Nebraska and after a few weeks with our president we feel ok looking for another foster for her. Mia really deserves a foster where she gets more individual attention while she continues to recover. She is a SWEET girl but she won't put up with anyone's nonsense, so while she's extremely dog friendly, she will tell a dog what's up when she feels it's needed. She a wonderful cuddle bug, enjoys wearing her doggie clothes and soaks up every bit of attention possible. She loves to nap in her kennel and is a perfect Netflix marathon companion! She's not a big barker and truly doesn't have any horrible habits that we have found. 

If you think that you could be the special foster home for miss Mia please contact us! 

To Contact Us

Message us through our website http://www.highplainspaw.org

Message the Facebook Page at https://www.facebook.com/HighPlainsPAW

Fill out our Foster Application at https://www.highplainspaw.org/foster-application

Email us at highplainspaw@gmail.com

Call our VOICEMAIL at (402)957-1578

WE DO NOT HAVE A FACILITY ALL OUR DOGS ARE LOCATED IN FOSTER HOMES. This means there is no place for you to go in person to view our dogs. We ask that an application be filled out and we will go from there!

Remmy is our diamond in the rough! She is shy and wary of new people at first, but with some time and treats, she will soon become your best friend.

We think she would do best with older children, and in a home without rabbits and/ or chickens. 

When brought into the office for some quiet time, Remmy did very well and enjoyed laying at our feet and chewing on her chew toy. 

She also walks great on leash! 

Remmy is available for adoption at the Fort Bragg Shelter. Please email Adriana at vegaa@mendocinocounty.org or call 707-961-2491 for more information.

animal.description:
Ready for the baste life!

Hey guys! My name is Mama Stuffin' and I am a 1 year old, female Terrier mix. I am a lap-sized, cuddly turkey at about 21 lbs. Like my name suggests, I am a mama! I was rescued by TAP from TJ, around Thanksgiving time, plump with puppies in my belly. I gave birth in a warm-as-oven home and my babies are all weaned and finding furever homes of their own! This mama is ready for her own feast and life. I am all bathroom and leash trained, and will be spayed soon!

When I was rescued, I left behind a bad situation of abuse. It left a bitter taste in my mouth, but I am ready to move along and get that sugary life. I am wary of people and get scared by quick movements by my foster family is helping me recover. They are also helping me realize that I don't need to resource guard as well, and will always have food in my life(and treats in my crate!) I am coming around and lovin' the attention being showered on me! I am learning to play and training is turning out to be good for me. Car rides make me sick, but medication helps. I am good with my foster siblings, a yorkie and a pittie mix, but can be selective specially if other dogs' get into arguments. I am not fond of horse-play, loud sounds and it makes me nervous when people or dogs fight. I just want the world to love! I am fiercely loyal and want to protect the fam. I would need a family who can show some patience to teach me that the world indeed is better than even a feasty spread!

I would love to be a part of a family who can love me unconditionally and patiently train me. I am eager to learn that I dont have to guarded or scared anymore! I will prefer to be a single dog and belong to an all-adults family. So let's bring on the drum(sticks) roll and meet up! My adoption fee is $350 and that includes spaying/neutering, shots, and microchip. If you want to take me home, please fill out the form on the website here: https://theanimalpad.org/adoption-application/

animal.description:
Hes a Matzo, Matzo man!

Hi there! My name is Matzo and Im bound to warm you up faster than a homecooked bowl of matzo soup! Im spunky, sweet, and a super snuggler. Im a 9-month-old, 46-pound, lab mix. Im already neutered and in pawfect health. I was recently rescued from the streets of Tijuana right around the holidays during Hanukkah to be exact. Life with my foster has been a whole latke fun, but what I really want is a furever home!

Im an active pooch who loves to play. Im the king of fetch, going on walks, and just running around outside. I adore my hoomans and get along with everyone I meet. I like kids too, but since I tend to jump, Id probably do best with the older ones. Even though I love people, I need to be socialized with other dogs. My ruff past has made me a bit defensive, so I need to learn that other pups can be my friend. I havent met any cats, so Im not sure what I think about them.

Even though Im an energetic guy, Im equally mellow at home. I never destroy things in the house when you leave, but when youre home Ill gladly nap by your side. Once youre done working, Im an all-star snuggler and will take cuddle and pets at any chance I get!

Im one smart cookie, so my training is going very well. Im already completely crate trained, house trained, and Im getting better on the leash with my gentle leader. I never get separation anxiety either. Like I said, I still need some work in the socialization department, but with some TLC & patience, Im sure Ill get there!

If youre looking for a playful pup who will go on all of lifes adventures with you, Im your guy! After the fun is done, Ill gladly be your cuddle buddy too. I think Id do best in a home without young children or other dogs as Im still learning the ropes. I hope we can continue my training together! I would love a yard, but as long as I get my exercise, Im a happy boy. So what do you say? Adopt this Mazto man today! My adoption fee is $450 and that includes spaying/neutering, shots, and microchip. If you want to take me home, please fill out the form on the website here: https://theanimalpad.org/adoption-application/

I am very friendly and get along great with all people and dogs, big or small. I do like kiddos but need to take care of my nipping first. Like the heart emoji, I am full of love and affection. I do like cuddling, but I am amore of an outside-yard player. No mountain is too high for me to scale, snow or shine! I really enjoy socialization at dog parks, long walks and play dates through the week.

I am a growing boy and would love a family who can accommodate a biggie older me. I love to be outdoorsy and energetic and will make a great companion for those long hikes. You can have a happy, energetic, loving cuddly emoji all in one with me! If you wanna take me home, give me a wave! My adoption fee is $500 and that includes spaying/neutering, shots, and microchip. animal.description:
Sarge is a year and half old male Great Dane. He is about 33 inches at the shoulder and came to MAGDRL a bit under his ideal weight. He lived with another male Great Dane and a 4 month old female pit bull pup. He and the other unaltered male were having disagreements from time to time so it would be best that he is placed with a laid-back female which we would routinely recommend anyway. He has not had any direct interaction with cats so he would be an unknown with them. He has lived with children between the ages of 9 and 18 and maybe a few days with a newborn. He has met women, men, and children with no issues. He did need some work on his manners as he tends to jump up when he gets excited, but his foster home is doing great work with him concerning this. He has had run of the house in the past, but he is being create trained at the present and he is taking to it well. Sarge walks pretty well on the leash, but he does have some what of a prey drive so the foster is working on this as well. He is very food motivated which helps to redirect his focus. He is very active and loves to play and learn new things. Sarge is getting along well with his foster brother who is a senior and not quite as playful as he is. He is quite athletic and has jumped over fences in the past to go exploring so he will need a minimum of a 5 ft fence to be places. Sarge has been given more structure that he had before he came to us and he is doing quite well with it so we would love for him to have an experienced leader to be able to give him the structure that he needs to be the best that he can be. Again, he is extremely food motivated so that will be very helpful to correct this behavior. Sarge is a super nice boy with a ton of potential to be a shining start in the lives of the perfect family. Sarge came to MAGDRL in December 2020 (2)



For more info on this dog and our adoption policies, visit PA MAGDRL at http://www.padanerescue.com. MAGDRL adopts Great Danes in NY, NJ, PA, MD, DE, DC, VA, & WV.

animal.description:
Meet Simon! Simon is an 8month old, 21 lbs. fox terrier mix. He does great around other dogs and is as loving as can be! Simon is new to the rescue, so stay tune for more updates!

If you’d like to meet Simon, the first step is to complete and submit an adoption application on our okwestierescue.com website and we’ll get the process started. 

Please allow 1-2 weeks to finish processing your application, but please know our volunteers are working hard on it. 

Simon’s adoption fee is $400 and is tax deductible. 

NOTE: You must complete and submit an application and be approved to adopt prior to being able to meet the dog.  The requested tax-deductible adoption donation is $400 for our puppies, $300 for up to age 7 and $150 for ages 8 and older.

We do not ship our pets.  Be prepared to travel to Tulsa, OK, or Oklahoma City, OK, or the location where this dog is fostered to pick up your dog in person if your application is approved.  Once you are approved, you may adopt any of our dogs that is a good fit. 

We are a non-profit organization that spends our adoption fees and donations on vaccinations, surgeries, various medical tests, medicines, food and supplies needed by our dogs. Our fees do not cover the overall expenses incurred by the care of our dogs, but they do help defray the costs involved.  We thank you for your support. 

Please Note: We are a RESCUE, which is different from a shelter. We conduct veterinary and personal reference checks during the application approval process. We always try to select the right applicant for each dog, based on the dog’s needs and try to find the best match for both dog and human.
We leave a dog’s profile online until either it has been adopted, has received several applications, or is not able to be adopted for some reason.

animal.description:
Are you looking for a classic beauty? That’s me, Maggie! I’m a 14-year-old, 12-pound, female chihuahua, fully vetted, vaccinated, and on heartworm preventative. I may be an older gal, but I’ve got a lot of love left to give! Are you interested?

My owner was recently placed in assisted living, so now I need a new family. I’m a friendly, affectionate girl, and I love to meet new people and follow my humans around. I especially enjoy napping at my foster mom’s feet as she works! I consider myself a bit of a foodie and will bark with joy when it looks like I’m going to get a treat or a meal. 

I do have a couple of minor problems that come along with my senior status. My teeth aren’t as strong as they used to be, so the rescue has me scheduled for dental surgery soon. I might need soft food afterward. I also need frequent potty breaks to prevent accidents in the house. I’m great about keeping my crate clean though, and I don’t mind hanging out in it if you need to leave me for a while.

You’ll love my beautiful long coat and my sweet disposition! If you’re looking for a low-energy, easygoing girl like me, I’d love to become your new shadow! 

Maggie’s adoption fee is $250. If you are interested in adopting Maggie, please DO NOT SEND A MESSAGE TO OUR RESCUE GROUP.  We are too busy placing dogs in great homes to answer messages and inquiries through the listing site. 

PLEASE GO TO THE LINK BELOW TO COMPLETE AN ADOPTION APPLICATION.
 
www.chihuahua-rescue.com/adoption-application
 
CRT requires an approved adoption application and a home visit for all adoption applicants.  CRT transports to OH, KY, IL, MI, MN, WI.
